{
  "name": "Hunting Trap",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>When you use your action to set it, this trap forms a saw-toothed steel ring that snaps shut when a creature steps on a pressure plate in the center. The trap is affixed by a heavy chain to an immobile object, such as a tree or a spike driven into the ground. A creature that steps on the plate must succeed on a [[/save dex 13 format=long]] or take 1d4 &amp;Reference[piercing]{piercing} damage and stop moving. Thereafter, until the creature breaks free of the trap, its movement is limited by the length of the chain (typically 3 feet long). A creature can use its action to make a DC 13 &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} check, freeing itself or another creature within its reach on a success. Each failed check deals 1 &amp;Reference[piercing]{piercing} damage to the trapped creature.</p>\n</div>",
